OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F419A1777539988
OL,3,CGraves identified of two missing
OL,4,Csoldiers more than a century later
OL,6,FThe previously un-named graves of two
OL,7,FSussex soldiers who gave their lives
OL,8,Fduring World War one have been
OL,9,Fidentified in Belgium.
OL,11,FLance Corporal William Voice MM, was
OL,12,Fborn in Horsham, in 1886 and served
OL,13,Fwith the 8th Battalion Queens Royal
OL,14,FWest Surrey Regiment.
OL,16,FAnd Lance Corporal Lionel Weller
OL,17,FSandell ` known to his family as
OL,18,FSolly, - was born in Worthing, in
OL,19,F1899. He served 10th Battalion Queens
OL,20,FOwn Royal West Kent Regiment.
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}   G1/7
OL,2,W,.!" ,.!+, "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,
